remarks: Not-free deduction for restricted uniqueness.  This is a version where ` x ` and ` y ` are distinct.  (Contributed by Jim Kingdon, 6-Jun-2018.)
statement:
nfreudxy.1 $e |- F/ y ph $.
nfreudxy.2 $e |- ( ph -> F/_ x A ) $.
nfreudxy.3 $e |- ( ph -> F/ x ps ) $.
nfreudxy $p |- ( ph -> F/ x E! y e. A ps ) $.
$d x y $.
